gentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Running the tool on a repository that has no commits yet produces an empty report rather than an error.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Minimal failing invariant: on a freshly initialized repo with zero commits, CLI returns an empty report and no fatal error. This depends on real git behavior for unborn HEAD and real subprocess exit/error text. A stubbed git client could hide the exact failure mode. Rejected higher levels: behavior is about git/CLI error handling only, not AI/ML decisions or agent pipelines.","test_description":"Initialize a new temp git repo without commits, run the CLI subprocess, assert successful completion and empty structured report on stdout.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.63,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The counts in the report match the actual change history of the repository being analyzed.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Minimal failing invariant: for a repo with known sequence of adds/deletes/renames/modifies, reported category counts equal the true git history-derived counts. The real failure boundary is end-to-end history extraction from actual repo state via git and CLI wiring; mocks risk validating only canned histories. Rejected higher levels: no AI/ML output quality dependency and no multi-step agentic reasoning in behavior text.","test_description":"Construct a temp repo with scripted commits producing known category totals, run CLI as subprocess, parse structured stdout, and compare each category count against expected totals from the scripted history.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.17,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The output is identical whether the changes being analyzed are staged or unstaged.","minimum_le